    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 Toast with Undo action" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md">
        Use `Toaster` + `useToastController` + action-button slot for Undo; timeout = 5000 ms.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Authenticated BFF zip download" location=".claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md">
        Use `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`; response.blob() → URL.createObjectURL → anchor.click().
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Optimistic UI rollback" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md">
        Apply state change immediately; queue server call; on success keep + show Undo toast; on failure revert + show error toast with Retry.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check">Verify context &lt; 60%. If higher, run `context-handoff` before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="0.5" name="Invoke fluent-v9-component">Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` (binding per design.md §6.0). Load `fluent-v9-component-authoring.md`, `fluent-v9-portal-gotcha.md`, `fluent-v9-theming.md`, `spaarke-sso-binding.md`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Load knowledge">Read ADR-006, ADR-021, ADR-022, ADR-028; PCF CLAUDE.md. Verify task 051 has shipped `POST /api/documents/bulk-download`. Read existing email pipeline + Xrm.WebApi usage in `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` to inventory existing patterns to reuse.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Create BulkActionBar component">Create `components/BulkActionBar.tsx`. Props: `{ selectedIds: string[], onClear: () =&gt; void, onEmail: () =&gt; void, onDownload: () =&gt; void, onPin: () =&gt; void, onDelete: () =&gt; void, onDocTypeChange: (newType: string) =&gt; void, onShareLink: () =&gt; void, docTypeOptions: TagFilterOption[] }`. Renders a sticky Fluent v9 `Toolbar` with `Badge` showing count, Clear button, and 6 `ToolbarButton` (or `MenuButton` for Doc Type).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Mount BulkActionBar in SemanticSearchControl">In `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`, conditionally render `&lt;BulkActionBar /&gt;` when `selection.size &gt;= 1`. Position it sticky above the list view column-header row; in card view, sticky at top of card grid. Clear handler resets `selection` state.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Wire Email selected">For single doc: open email composer with the SPE file as attachment (reuse existing Email handler from per-row 3-dot menu). For multi-doc: invoke the existing email pipeline extended for zip-attachment case — implementer note: this may require a small server-side enhancement (out of scope here; if blocked, escalate per CLAUDE.md §6).</step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire Download selected">Call `authenticatedFetch('/api/documents/bulk-download', { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify({ documentIds: [...selection] }) })`. On 200: response.blob() → URL.createObjectURL → anchor.click() with filename from `Content-Disposition`. On 413: show error toast "Maximum 500 documents per bulk download". On other failures: show error toast with Retry.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire Pin selected">For each id in selection, add to `pinnedIds` (existing state from task 041) and persist to localStorage key `spaarke.docs.pinned.{userId}.{matterId}`. Show success toast "N documents pinned".</step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire Delete selected">Open Fluent v9 confirmation `Dialog`: "Delete N selected documents?". On confirm: bulk Xrm.WebApi `delete` for each id. Show success toast on completion. On any per-doc failure: show error toast with the failed ids.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Wire Document Type → selected with optimistic UI">Render a `MenuButton` "Document Type" with `MenuItem` per `sprk_documenttype` option (reuse `docTypeOptions` from task 042's metadata fetch). On select: (a) immediately update `documentType` in client-side `results` state for each selected id (optimistic); (b) call `Xrm.WebApi.updateRecord` for each in parallel; (c) on success: show Toast "N documents updated to {type}" with **5s Undo** action button that reverts state + calls bulk update back to original values; (d) on failure: revert client state + show error Toast with Retry button.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Wire Share link">For each selected id, build URL `https://{env}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?etn=sprk_document&amp;id={guid}&amp;pagetype=entityrecord`. Compose email body `{DocName} → {URL}\n` per doc. Open mailto: or Outlook composer with this body. Do NOT attach SPE files (per spec — Share link is for Dataverse record URLs only).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Toaster wiring">Add `Toaster` to PCF root (or wherever the existing toast surface lives — verify). Use `useToastController` hook to dispatch toasts from action handlers.</step>
    <step order="11" name="Dark-mode + a11y check">Run PCF in dev harness with `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`. Verify bar + toolbar buttons + toasts + confirmation Dialog render with v9 tokens. Run axe scan in both themes.</step>
    <step order="12" name="Build verification">Run `npm run build:prod` from PCF root.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">Invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check`. Resolve all findings. `code-review` will verify `authenticatedFetch` usage on bulk-download call.</step>
    <step order="13" name="Checkpoint">Run `context-handoff` (silent: ✅ Checkpoint).</step>
    <step order="14" name="Update task tracking">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 045 status 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task (046).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
